abstract: Mayor Gavin Newsom has recently stepped out of the limelight in the debate on same-sex marriage, but the impact on his campaign for lieutenant governor is unclear.
snippet: Mayor Gavin Newsom has recently stepped out of the limelight in the debate on same-sex marriage, but the impact on his campaign for lieutenant governor is unclear.
lead_paragraph: On the night of Aug. 4, after a federal district judge struck down Proposition 8, California’s ban on same-sex marriage, a gaggle of San Francisco politicians worked their way up the City Hall steps to rally the jubilant crowd of 800 that was roaring its approval for the landmark ruling.

abstract: The union that represents players in Major League Soccer recently released a list of player salaries for the 2010 season.
snippet: The union that represents players in Major League Soccer recently released a list of player salaries for the 2010 season.
lead_paragraph: Under cover of the World Cup and amid Major League Soccer’s first break for it, the union that represents the North American league’s players has released its list of salaries for the 406 players under contract in 2010. And while the world’s most highly compensated soccer players scurry across the fields of South Africa, the more modestly paid M.L.S. players, where the average pay package is $138,169, down 6.6 percent from last season’s $147,945, are preparing to return to action this weekend.

abstract: A plan to make sitting or lying on a San Francisco sidewalk illegal in many circumstances is a direct result of a vicious assault last December, but the assault victim does not support the proposal.

lead_paragraph: Every fire begins with a spark. For San Francisco’s controversial proposed sit/lie law, the inciting incident happened on a Wednesday night in early December in the Haight  an act of violence so brutal it inspired a grass-roots movement.

abstract: An unlikely pair, a Republican district attorney and a criminal-defense lawyer, may be the key to reform in California.
snippet: An unlikely pair, a Republican district attorney and a criminal-defense lawyer, may be the key to reform in California.
lead_paragraph: One day last fall, Norman Williams sat drinking hot chocolate with his lawyer, Michael Romano, at a Peet’s coffee in Palo Alto, Calif. At an outdoor table, Williams began to talk about how he’d gone from serving a life sentence at Folsom State Prison to sitting there in the sun. “After being shut down for so many years. I didn’t believe it,” he said of the judge’s decision to release him in April 2009.

abstract: A selection of stories of interest to residents of the Bay Area.
snippet: A selection of stories of interest to residents of the Bay Area.
lead_paragraph: Telsa and Toyota to Build Electric Cars at Nummi Plant | Electric car manufacturing is coming to Fremont. Tesla Motors announced on Thursday that it would work with Toyota to build its Model S sedan, an all-electric vehicle, at the shuttered Nummi plant. The deal is expected to create more than 1,000 jobs. Toyota will invest $50 million in Tesla, which will buy the plant, where it plans to produce 20,000 electric vehicles a year. The cars are to have a range of 300 miles and sell for $50,000. The operation will occupy a small part of the plant, leaving room for more models to be made there in the future. [The San Jose Mercury News]
